/svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 27, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sse1719818928383.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sse1719818928383.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sse1719818928383.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"son1665702604460\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      $curkey\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"son1665702604460___curkey_256347\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the number of the current key in a validateKey or leaveModifiedKey trigger.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"son1665702604460__topic_d81374e1_d81375e1_d81376e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"son1665702604460__p_d81377e1_d81378e1_d81379e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$curkey</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"son1665702604460__topic_d53637e1_d53638e1_d53639e1_d53640e1_d53641e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d956146e66\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"son1665702604460__table_d8183e1_d8184e1_d8185e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values Returned by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$curkey</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"son1665702604460__table_d8183e1_d8184e1_d8185e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Value \n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"son1665702604460__table_d8183e1_d8184e1_d8185e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"son1665702604460__table_d8183e1_d8184e1_d8185e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">\n 1\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"son1665702604460__table_d8183e1_d8184e1_d8185e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Primary key\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"son1665702604460__table_d8183e1_d8184e1_d8185e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">\n &gt;1\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"son1665702604460__table_d8183e1_d8184e1_d8185e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Key number of a candidate key\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"son1665702604460__table_d8183e1_d8184e1_d8185e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">\n \"\"\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"son1665702604460__table_d8183e1_d8184e1_d8185e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n An error occurred\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"son1665702604460__table_d8186e1_d8187e1_d8188e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> following\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$curkey</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"son1665702604460__table_d8186e1_d8187e1_d8188e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Value \n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"son1665702604460__table_d8186e1_d8187e1_d8188e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Error constant\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"son1665702604460__table_d8186e1_d8187e1_d8188e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"son1665702604460__table_d8186e1_d8187e1_d8188e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-1304</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"son1665702604460__table_d8186e1_d8187e1_d8188e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UPROCERR_UNKNOWN_CONTEXT&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"son1665702604460__table_d8186e1_d8187e1_d8188e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\"> Function not allowed, unknown\n                        context. For example, <code class=\"ph codeph\">$curkey</code> was encountered in an\n                        incorrect trigger. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"son1665702604460__topic_d53642e1_d53643e1_d53644e1_d53645e1_d53646e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d956146e196\">\n                       \n Use\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"son1665702604460__p_d81386e1_d81387e1_d81388e1\">Allowed only in a validateKey or leaveModifiedKey trigger.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"son1665702604460__p_d81389e1_d81390e1_d81391e1\">Allowed in all component types, except self-contained Reports.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"son1665702604460__topic_d53647e1_d53648e1_d53649e1_d53650e1_d53651e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d956146e208\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"son1665702604460__p_d81395e1_d81396e1_d81397e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$curkey</span> function returns the key number in the current occurrence for which the validateKey or leaveModifiedKey trigger was activated.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"son1665702604460__section_d51_nll_xbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d956146e221\">Example: Validating Keys and Error Handling</h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">The following example uses the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$curkey</span> function to\n               perform specific validation for each key and otherwise reports the error and context\n               using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerrorcontext</span>.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"son1665702604460__pre_slw_4ll_xbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger validateKey\nselectcase $curkey\n case 1 ;perform validation for the primary key\n ...\n case 2 ;perform validation for candidate key #2\n...\n case 4 ;perform validation for candidate key #4\n...\n elsecase\n message \"Error %%$procerror occurred at %%$procerrorcontext\"\n message \"Context: %%$dataerrorcontext\"\nendselectcase\nend; validateKey</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lrk1665702576500.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Validate</a><p>Determines whether the valerr data processing attribute is added for the selected entity node in the DTD tree. This attribute holds the occurrence or field validation error (depending on whether the selected item is an entity or field). Valid values are True or False (default).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fdp1665702576817.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>validatekey</a><p>Validate a key of the current occurrence.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bwv1665702576896.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>validateocc</a><p>Validate an occurrence.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/upd1665702601935.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$keytype</a><p>Return the type of the specified key.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wcw1719485700746.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$keyvalidation</a><p>Identify whether a primary or candidate key requires validation.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/epv1719810593542.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$totkeys</a><p>Return the total number of keys for an entity.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jqe1665702576424.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$dataerrorcontext</a><p>Return the context of the last validation error.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/emi1665702599671.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger leaveModifiedKey</a><p>Location for ProcScript that determines what happens after a key (especially a compound key) of an occurrence is modified. Applicable only in form components.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/frh1665703129863.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger validateKey</a><p>System trigger that defines the procedural checks to validate a modified primary or candidate key.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7423654\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7423654\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$curkey Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 27, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $curkey Return the number of the current key in a validateKey or leaveModifiedKey trigger. $curkey Return Values Table 1. Values Returned by $curkey Value Meaning 1 Primary key >1 Key number of a candidate key \"\" An error occurred Table 2. Values returned by $procerror following $curkey Value Error constant Meaning -1304 <UPROCERR_UNKNOWN_CONTEXT> Function not allowed, unknown context. For example, $curkey was encountered in an incorrect trigger. Use Allowed only in a validateKey or leaveModifiedKey trigger. Allowed in all component types, except self-contained Reports. Description The $curkey function returns the key number in the current occurrence for which the validateKey or leaveModifiedKey trigger was activated. Example: Validating Keys and Error Handling The following example uses the $curkey function to perform specific validation for each key and otherwise reports the error and context using $procerror and $procerrorcontext . trigger validateKey selectcase $curkey case 1 ;perform validation for the primary key ... case 2 ;perform validation for candidate key #2 ... case 4 ;perform validation for candidate key #4 ... elsecase message \"Error %%$procerror occurred at %%$procerrorcontext\" message \"Context: %%$dataerrorcontext\" endselectcase end; validateKey Copy Related Links Validate Determines whether the valerr data processing attribute is added for the selected entity node in the DTD tree. This attribute holds the occurrence or field validation error (depending on whether the selected item is an entity or field). Valid values are True or False (default). validatekey Validate a key of the current occurrence. validateocc Validate an occurrence. $keytype Return the type of the specified key. $keyvalidation Identify whether a primary or candidate key requires validation. $totkeys Return the total number of keys for an entity. $dataerrorcontext Return the context of the last validation error. trigger leaveModifiedKey Location for ProcScript that determines what happens after a key (especially a compound key) of an occurrence is modified. Applicable only in form components. trigger validateKey System trigger that defines the procedural checks to validate a modified primary or candidate key. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}